{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position, weigh in potatoes, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>50 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Carefully remove Varoma lid and add broccoli, secure Varoma lid and steam a further <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>.","Remove Varoma. Quickly slice potatoes in half lengthwise and set aside to cool slightly. Rinse mixing bowl with cold water and dry thoroughly.","Preheat oven to 375°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside.","Place cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Scoop out and reserve the potato flesh leaving a ¼ inch border (see Tip), being careful not to pierce the skin. Transfer potato skins to prepared baking sheet and set aside.","Place steamed potato flesh (approx. 14 oz), steamed broccoli, ¾ of the reserved grated cheese (approx. 5 oz), yogurt, butter, milk, salt, pepper and paprika into mixing bowl and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning and if necessary mix a further <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Brush the outside of potato skins with oil and sprinkle with salt, for a crispier skin.","Spoon potato mixture into potato skin shells. Bake potatoes for 20 minutes (375°F), then top with remaining grated cheese and bake for 5-10 minutes (375°F) or until cheese melts. Garnish with chopped chives and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 oz water","2 russet potatoes, large (approx. 28-32 oz total), washed","6 oz broccoli florets","7 oz sharp cheddar cheese, cubed","6 oz plain Greek yogurt","4 oz unsalted butter, softened, cubed","2 oz whole milk","½ tsp salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste","½ tsp paprika","salt, to season (optional)","ground black pepper, to season (optional)","1 tbsp olive oil","salt, to sprinkle potato skins","fresh chives, for garnish, minced"]}],"id":"r359672","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-rEHx6RnVquc\/XZVPoqfctZI\/AAAAAAAAc68\/uxk90TFeZhc14CwkiYN9nQ8iYrR6U-2fACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BHlcmFuTREYpmPeF.png","title":"Broccoli and Cheddar Baked Potatoes","publishedAt":"2018-06-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19 g","fat":"52 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"39 g","calories":"2895 kJ \/ 692 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, parchment paper, basting brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To scoop out potato flesh, use a paring knife to score the potato halves, leaving a border (approx. ¼ in. thick). Then use a spoon to carefuly scoop out the flesh.","If potato skin is compromised or too thin to hold the filling, create a foil boat by scrunching a strip of foil and shaping around the potato skin before adding filling.","Make the potato mixture ahead and stuff the shells just before baking.","Garnish with sour cream or plain yogurt."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 25m","4 pieces"]}